Algeria to Invest $35 Billion by 2021 to Increase Power Capacity

-- B y   S a l a h   S l i m a n i
-- 
2011-10-10T17:28:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/algeria-to-invest-35-billion-by-2021-to-increase-power-capacity.html
Algeria  will invest about 2,600
billion dinars ($35 billion) by 2021 to increase power capacity,
said Noureddine Bouterfa, Chief Executive Officer of state-run
Societe Algerienne de lâ€™Electricite et du Gaz.  The country will allocate 1,500 billion dinars of that
amount to renewable energy, Bouterfa said at a conference in
Algiers. Algeria, a member of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries, will add a total of 13,800 megawatts of
capacity, including 3,400 megawatts at a renewable energy park.  -Editors: Rachel Graham, Raj Rajendran  To contact the reporter on this story:
